      <akn:section eId="sec_28_4805_05">
        <akn:num>28-4805.05</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Income taxes.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-4805_05_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A tax required to be paid by a trustee based on receipts allocated to income shall be paid from income.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-4805_05_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A tax required to be paid by a trustee based on receipts allocated to principal shall be paid from principal, even if the tax is called an income tax by the taxing authority.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-4805_05_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A tax required to be paid by a trustee on the trust’s share of an entity’s taxable income shall be paid:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28-4805_05_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>After applying subsections (a) through (c) of this section, the trustee shall adjust income or principal receipts to the extent that the trust’s taxes are reduced because the trust receives a deduction for payments made to a beneficiary.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
